                     <!--This info to go in the introduction? 
                     <p>The Tretiz is found at the end of this C13/14 volume, which the BL describes
                        as a 'Miscellany of theological, grammatical and historical texts'. It
                        corresponds very closely to the text and glosses in MS T, although it does
                        not transmit all of the glosses found in MS T. The text is incomplete, filling only two
                        folios of between 30 and 32 lines per page (32 for fol. 101r; 30 for fols.
                        101v-102v).</p>
                     <p>The text is executed in a notably cursive-influenced hand distinctive from
                        those before it in the volume. There are several apparent pen-trials for the
                        'e' character, likely by the same scribe, on fol. 102v.</p>
                     <p>Space for unexecuted initials have been left on ll. 1, 35, 100; in the
                        latter two cases, the guide-letter is visible.</p>-->
                     </supportDesc></objectDesc>
               </physDesc>
               <history>
